The paper deals with the issue of consistency models in databases and their impact on program correctness. This topic is closely related to database systems (cs.DB) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the reduction of the verification problem to a state reachability problem, which is a common technique in distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses proof techniques for verifying program correctness, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE).
